    <IRS990ScheduleO documentId="RetDoc1044400001">
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>FORM 990 PART V LINE 2A AND 2B</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>PALOMAR HEALTH FOUNDATION DOES NOT FILE ANY FORM W-2'S DIRECTLY. EMPLOYEES WORKING WITHIN PALOMAR HEALTH FOUNDATION SHARE A COMMON PAYMASTER WITH PALOMAR HEALTH THE ENTITY THE FOUNDATION HAS A MANAGEMENT SERVICES AGREEMENT WITH. PALOMAR HEALTH FILES ALL RELATED FEDERAL EMPLOYMENT TAX RETURNS.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 3</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>THE ORGANIZATION HAS A MANAGEMENT SERVICES AGREEMENT WITH PALOMAR HEALTH. THE SERVICES PROVIDED INCLUDE ADMINISTRATIVE AND FINANCIAL MANAGEMENT SERVICES AND MARKETING/PUBLIC RELATIONS. KRISTIN GASPAR THE PRESIDENT/CEO IS COMPENSATED BY PALOMAR HEALTH VIA THE MANAGEMENT SERVICES AGREEMENT, HER FISCAL YEAR COMPENSATION WAS $159,849 REPORTED ON FORM 990 PART IX LINE 5.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>THE PRESIDENT AND THIRD PARTY ACCOUNTANTS WILL REVIEW THE FORM 990 PRIOR TO FILING.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY IS REVIEWED DURING THE INITIAL ORIENTATION OF ANY OFFICER, DIRECTOR, AND KEY EMPLOYEE. THE POLICY IS THEN REVIEWED WITH EACH PERSON OF AN ANNUAL BASIS.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
